er and I about money and effort vs. reward. While they did a good job about teaching us values like friendship, honesty, generosity and other things, they totally missed the boat on motivation and money. Both my brother and are adults, but neither of us has the slightest clue on how to manage money. Neither of us will probably ever be able to buy a house because of how bad our credit is.<br><br>I guess what I'm saying is, be consistent with the rewards and don't relent if the child does not fulfil their part of the bargain. Once they have the money, make sure you provide them with little lessons on how to manage the money. How to save it. Etc. <br> <p><center><a href="http://ang.mux.net"> <img src="http://ang.mux.net/jasi2.jpg" border=0></a><br><img src="http://home.rochester.rr.com/dotu/highbs.jpg" border=0> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usatanstolemypepsi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SatanStolemypepsi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.puffandstuff.at/symbols/horuseye.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 3:56:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Paying for report cards/grades</span><hr size=1> its simply posistive reienforcement...<br><br><br>which is better then negative by far in building self esteem..but one has to wonder about the value message conveyed. <br><br>Does is teach children that learning is good for the cash flow or for the prize of knowledge?<br><br>Its tricky...some will realize its just a reward for a job well done...but sometimes that reward mentality becomes ingrained; and later on if suitable rewards arent given for what they believe to