file?language=EN>Wende Darling</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I was raised by a <br>travelling Japenese<br>Karaoke band</span><br>  Posts: 2105<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/1/02 3:07:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/images/friends/shrunk.jpg HEIGHT=150 WIDTH=175></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Paying for report cards/grades</span><hr size=1> and mine too, Honey...mine too... <p><center>Wende Darling<BR>Lev 56 Dark Elf Cleric<BR>and her eyes, oh, her eyes, had every season of leaf in them:<BR>the twin greens of spring and high summer, the golds of autumn,<BR>and, in her rages, black midwinter rot</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uakashamia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>akashamia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/akashamia1/morg.html" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/1/02 10:14:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Paying for report cards/grades</span><hr size=1> Hi Wende,  I have thought about this often.  Being a hairdressier, I speak to a LOT of women and grandparents.  While I find its more the grandparents doing this, some parents do this too.  Personally I dont think children should be paid for good grades.  This is something they should do because they take pride in themselves. <br><br> I equate it to responsibility.  Ok you guys are going to rant me about this, but I dont believe in paying our children for helping out around the house.   My job is work, cook and do most of the cleaning.  Same with my spouse.  The children have thier jobs to do.  We all pitch in to help each other because thats what family is about.  Its not about what we can get out of each other.  Paying a child to help around the house is obsurd.  Allowance bah.  I wouldnt pay my husband for stuff he does why should I pay my children. <br><br>Now your all gonna jump on the band wagon about teaching the value of money.  How are they going to learn to earn things.  That money does not grow on trees and when its gone oh well you spent it.<br><br>I think family values are more important than money.  That as a family we all work together to make our lives easier.  When the child is a teenager there are part time jobs they can get.  This is when the child learns the value of a dollar.  <br><br>Ya know somewhere along the way the old values of family unity has been lost.  The Orientals really have a stronge sense of family.  What it means to be family. We Americans stick our parents in homes when they get old.  We pay our children for things that should just be understood that, thats what you do because you are a member of this family.<br><br>Well thats my 2 pp worth.<br><br>Morgania.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvoide.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Voide</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/1/02 6:24:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmmm...</span><hr size=1> As a child that just completed high school, and is continuing college, let me see if I can share some knowledge.<br><br>I graduated high school with a 2.7 overall GPA, as an extremely unmotivated student. I should have easily gotten at least a 3.5 GPA, but I did little to no work because I did not care to.<br><br>Trying to motivate kids that are unmotivated to begin with, is certaintly a tricky thing to do, almost bordering on impossible. However, I do not know your children Wende, they might be very motivated to do well already, and you are just trying to bolster their esteem, so I will speak from my own experience.<br><br>If they are unmotivated, like myself, no amount of bribes or treats is going to get them going again.  External motivation will not work on an unmotivated child, they need to be internally motivated themselves.  If this is the case, just try opening up their eyes to the big picture of life, i.e. getting good grades usually helps you get into a good college and get a good job for the most part. Other than that, there is not really much you can do to instill internal motivation in a child, as it is hard to come by.<br><br>In summary, if they are all ready motivated, pay then all you want! If they are not motivated, try to show them what happens when they aren't! I'm sure we all know someone that had big plans for life and then got them ruined by poor grades. As I've said, this is just my experience from an unmotivated but trying, 19 year old college student.<br><br>Voide Bloodrune<br>Halfling Rogue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uebine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ebine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/2/02 12:38:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmm...</span><hr size=1> Money isnt very good thing to motivate kids with. Look at real life work. If everyone got a $1 an hour raise would you see anyone be more productive. Maybe a few but not all. The best way in my idea is to sit down and ask your child what they would like and develop a plan with them. Say a young child might really want a better bike. So you draw up a contract on what needs to be done to get it. Something that brings enjoyment that you got on your own gives you more a sense of pride(depending on the child)  Although I think I would base big items on more than one report card. In the end you will have to tailor your plan that best suits your child. I like one of the posters sat around and did nothing in math and would ace every test. The guy beside me did all his homework and got Fs. So if your child is getting Ds then alter it and say if you get a 2.6. Once they get to that level raise them to the next. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminutemanaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minute Manaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ASSIST DAMMIT!!!</span><br>  Posts: 1527<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/2/02 10:16:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmm...</span><hr size=1> It doesn't necessarily need to be money though.  I remember when our next door neighbor Ms. Winona (who was 87 years old) used to take us for a banana split at the drive in if we brought her a 100% on a test.  I remember actually trying harder because I wanted to get my banana split, but even more so I wanted to feel that pride that came with presenting the 100% to her.<br><br>Motivation is not a bad thing.  Hell even grown, if I know that I'm going to get some incentive for doing more sales, I'm going to work harder to sale more.  If I don't, I am still going to do my job, but would be more reluctant to put in that extra step.<br><br>Money, Banana Splits, Extra Play Time, whatever.  Nothing wrong with rewarding for doing well. <p><br>Minute Manaslayer<br>60th Sage Charmer<br>Realm Brell Serilis<br><a href="mailto:Minute@midsouth.rr.com">My E-Mail</a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42859">My Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukosaghn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kosaghn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/2/02 10:37:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmm...</span><hr size=1> Hehehe My mother bought me a D&amp;D module everytime I got an &quot;A&quot; on my report card...<br><br>what a geek...<br><br>.KOS <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushoshannahswordsinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shoshannah Swordsinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/2/02 3:30:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=635.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.uk.zelda.com/seasons_uk/images/char_din.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmm...</span><hr size=1> I didn't vote, because well....you should do what your comfortable doing.<br><br>In my house we reward my daughter depending on the situation.  She has a smart mouth (wonder where that came from), so every week she comes home with a g